olive oil
1 packet basmati rice
1 packet portabello mushrooms
1 packet teriyaki sauce
2 tbs soy sauce
½ tbs brown sugar
1 packet beef mince
1 bag Asian Stir-Fry Mix
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet sesame dressing
1 packet roasted peanuts

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes.
• Drain and set aside.

• Thinly slice portabello mushrooms.
• In a small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, the soy sauce and brown sugar. Set aside.

Little cooks: Kids can help combine the sauces!

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook mushrooms and beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 6-7 minutes.
• Add Asian stir-fry mix and cook until browned, 2-3 minutes.
• Add ginger paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add teriyaki sauce mixture and stir until the beef is coated, 30 seconds.

• Divide basmati rice between bowls.
• Top with teriyaki beef and mushrooms. Garnish with roasted peanuts.
• Drizzle with sesame dressing to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch and drizzle over the dressing.